SIMPLE: pastern
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pastern
<hw>Pas"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of.
<ets>pasturon</ets>, F. <ets>p⟦acir⟧turon</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>pasture</ets> a tether, for beasts while pasturing; prop., a
pasturing. See <er>Pasture</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The part of the
foot of the horse, and allied animals, between the fetlock and the
coffin joint. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Horse</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The upper bone, or phalanx, of the foot is called the
<stype>great pastern bone</stype>; the second, the <stype>small pastern
bone</stype>; and the third, in the hoof, the <stype>coffin
bone</stype>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pastern joint</b></col>, <cd>the joint in the hoof of the
horse, and allied animals, between the great and small pastern
bones.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A shackle for horses while pasturing.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A patten.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>paste-up</ent>⟦br⟧
